    <briefdescription>
<para>Interface used to provide custom focus algorithm for retrieving the next focusable view. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The application / ui can implement the interface and override the focus behaviour. Upon providing an implementation of this interface, the PreFocusChangeSignal is no longer emitted. If focus is changing within a layout container, then the layout container is queried first to provide the next focusable view. If this does not provide a valid view, then the <ref refid="classDali_1_1Ui_1_1FocusManager" kindref="compound">FocusManager</ref> will check focusable properties to determine next focusable view. If focusable properties are not set, then the <ref refid="classDali_1_1Ui_1_1FocusManager" kindref="compound">FocusManager</ref> calls the <ref refid="classDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelFocusManager_1_1CustomAlgorithmInterface_1a83e3123ddd2414c4635b904c773f684f" kindref="member">GetNextFocusableView()</ref> method of this interface. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
